This is the complete run of the Marvel Knights' incarnation of Fantastic Four, written by the excellent Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa (Afterlife with Archie). Though competing with Mark Waid's famous run on the main title, RAS managed to craft his own compelling story - exploring the familiar themes and dynamics of family while also showing FF stalwarts like Namor in a new light. Though cancelled after issue 30, RAS managed to complete a pretty good run, although it seems now it is very difficult to find this anywhere. At least now this torrent rectifies that problem! ;-)

Thanks to all the scanners (including Team DCP) and original uploaders, and of course please seed. Enjoy! :-) 

This fills a request for AlternityTom. Also, for me personally, ha!
